The paper is about semantic image segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the trade-off between accuracy and tractability in modeling, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a discriminatively trained re-ranking model also suggests a focus on classification and pattern recognition (cs.CL). Finally, the evaluation of the approach on benchmark datasets indicates a focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
